messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /api/paste

All HTTP methods acceptable:
- false

Per-method acceptability (based on the code, not runtime framework behavior):

- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The controller class is annotated with @RequestMapping("/api/paste"), so every method-level mapping is rooted at /api/paste.
- The method postNewCodePasteWith is annotated with @PostMapping with no path attribute, therefore its full path is /api/paste and it explicitly accepts POST.
- No @RequestMapping/@*Mapping for this exact path declares any other HTTP method (HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, PUT, DELETE, PATCH). Per the instruction to base acceptability on the code (not on framework defaults like automatic HEAD/OPTIONS handling), those methods are considered not acceptable for this endpoint.
- Other handler methods exist in the same controller (e.g., @GetMapping("/{paste_id}"), @DeleteMapping("/{paste_id}"), @GetMapping("/public")), but they map to different paths (/api/paste/{paste_id} and /api/paste/public) and do not change the allowed methods for /api/paste (the POST endpoint).
